creenFromWeb?topicID=1821.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Deciding on Race (Iksar vs Barbarian)</span><hr size=1> If you're going for uberness, go iksar. If you're getting bashed by a mob at the endgame, something is horribly wrong, so the AC bonus to lessen ripostle damage combined with regen makes Iksar ideal. In fact, Iksar at lvl 60 make just about the best race for any of their available classes, as they can wear Velious quest armor,  with the exception of warrior, because they can be stunned. <br>
<br>
If you're going for ease of play, and are intimidated by a serious challenge, go barbarian. Especially if you don't have a lot of time to play. A lot of these guys suggesting Iksar have lvl 55+ mains and spend about 8 hrs playing EQ per day. The 20 percent doesn't show up much when you play 6-8 hrs, but when you play 10 hrs a week, it hurts a lot.<br>
<br>
I personally chose Vah Shir. I wanted one, and already had an alt of every other class they could be, so I made one. Haven't really regretted it since. The Safe Fall is nice, although we get lev, so it's not that big of a deal, just a nice feature. As I understand, we are also the only beastlord race to get sneak, which is nice for getting those dubious merchants to sell to you. However, the main major downside is travelling. It's HARD to get out of Luclin at a young age if you don't have a guild or some friends to come get you, and the mobs there are pretty much insane, especially the ones in Hollowshade, so you should probably get out asap, if you can. I've found that my BL is very well liked, since beastlords are a neutral race, and must be agnostic. However, we can't fit into wood elf doors, same as barbarians, so if you spend a lot of time in Firiona Vie, this may be a concern.<br>
<br>
Slightly off-topic, Vah Shir make AWESOME bards. I have a 41 half elf bard, and it's to the point that once I get my enchanter to 60 and my BL to around 55, I might consider re-rolling him as a Vah Shir, simply because they sooo outclass any other bard race.<br>
