<br>
Barbarians - Tons of facial models<br>
Vah Shir - quite a few different skins (aka colors, stripes,ect)<br>
<br>
Ogres, Trolls, and Iksars - very few distinct facial options. <br>
<br>
Ictus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uredgiki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>redgiki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FF0000><CENTER>Beast Lord</FONT></CENTER></span><br>  Posts: 274<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/8/02 10:32:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1821.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looks</span><hr size=1> Love my Iksar Beastlord.  She's 48, very nearly 49.  Some people love the look of our (FEMALE) warders, some people hate them.  Reasons not to pick an Iksar:<br>
<br>
1.  The faction, as mentioned.  Big freaking deal, just gives me more targets to slaughter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   However, Sol B is a great dungeon to solo in from 39-48, so maybe you might want to get good faction in Neriak or something.  Spend a lot of time at the pub there socializing with the patrons and buying them drinks...<br>
2.  The XP penalty is VERY noticeable from the forties onward.  Identical play times with friends and they will outlevel you in the forties.  The pet damage fix mitigates this a ton, and makes Beastlords pretty fast levellers now<br>
3.  You think the pet is ugly, or don't like having a female pet.<br>
<br>
The reasons to pick an Iksar have been outlined above.  I never picked my Beastlord race on stats or faction.  I just picked one I thought would have the coolest-looking pet.  And she does look COOL.  I XP a lot with a Vah Shir Beastlord friend, and for some odd reason no matter where we park the pets, eventually they drift on top of one another.  I wonder what the puppies/kittens would look like... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1821.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1821.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1821.topic&index=25><img src=http://www.brentcopeland.com/beastlord/images/messageboard/BL_add_reply2.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1821.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.threadControl?topicID=1821.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1821.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1821.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub115.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jum